In [2]:
step = 0.1
pos = -8

f = lambda x: 1.5 * np.sin(x) + 0.25 * x*x
df = lambda x: 1.5 * np.cos(x) + 0.5* x

x = np.linspace(-10, 10, 100)
y = f(x)

positions = [pos]

for i in range(50):
    pos -= df(pos) * step
    positions.append(pos)

def init():
    line.set_data([], [])
    return line,

def animate(i):
    x_n = positions[i]
    y_n = f(x_n)
    line.set_data(x_n, y_n)
    return line

fig = plt.figure(figsize=(10, 6))

ax = plt.axes(xlim=(-10, 10), ylim=(-10, 20))

ax.plot(x,y, linewidth=4)

line, = ax.plot([], [], "D", marker='o', markersize=12)

animation.FuncAnimation(fig, animate, init_func=init, frames=len(positions), interval=200)

step = 0.1
pos = [-7, 7]

f = lambda x, y: x*x  + y*y
dfx = lambda x, y: 2 * x
dfy = lambda x, y: 2 * y

# If graph resolution is bad change last argument here.
xs = np.linspace(-10 , 10, 10)
ys = np.linspace(-10 , 10, 10)

X, Y = np.meshgrid(xs, ys)

Z = f(X, Y)

positions = [pos]

for i in range(50):
    x, y = pos
    pos[0] -= dfx(x, y) * step
    pos[1] -= dfy(x, y) * step
    positions.append(pos)    
    
def init():
    line.set_data([], [], [])
    return line,

def animate(i):
    x_n = positions[i][0]
    y_n = positions[i][1]
    z_n = f(x_n, y_n)
    graph = ax.scatter(x_n, y_n, z_n)
    return (graph)

fig = plt.figure(figsize=(10, 6))
ax = fig.add_subplot(111, projection='3d')

ax.plot_surface(X, Y, Z, rstride=1, cstride=1, color='b', alpha=0.4)

ax.view_init(elev=40, azim=30)
